{
  "page": "Most Devout",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Great_septon_of_Baelor_by_MarcSimonetti.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/8/8b/Great_septon_of_Baelor_by_MarcSimonetti.jpg/350px-Great_septon_of_Baelor_by_MarcSimonetti.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"263\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/8/8b/Great_septon_of_Baelor_by_MarcSimonetti.jpg/525px-Great_septon_of_Baelor_by_MarcSimonetti.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/8/8b/Great_septon_of_Baelor_by_MarcSimonetti.jpg/700px-Great_septon_of_Baelor_by_MarcSimonetti.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Great_septon_of_Baelor_by_MarcSimonetti.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The <a href=\"/index.php/Great_Sept_of_Baelor\" title=\"Great Sept of Baelor\">Great Sept of Baelor</a>, by Marc Simonetti ©</div></div></div>\n<p>The <b>Most Devout</b> are a council of the highest ranking clergy of the <a href=\"/index.php/Faith_of_the_Seven\" title=\"Faith of the Seven\">Faith of the Seven</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#About\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">About</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Feast_for_Crows\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Known_members_of_the_Most_Devout\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Known members of the Most Devout</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Historical_Most_Devout\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Historical Most Devout</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Most_Devout_during_A_Song_of_Ice_and_Fire\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Most Devout during <i>A Song of Ice and Fire</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#Notes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Notes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-10\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">7</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"About\">About</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Most_Devout&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: About\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The Most Devout can be identified by their cloth-of-<a href=\"/index.php/Silver\" title=\"Silver\">silver</a> vestments and crystal coronals.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Although the <a href=\"/index.php/High_Septon\" title=\"High Septon\">High Septon</a> is usually <a href=\"/index.php/Elections\" title=\"Elections\">elected</a> from among the Most Devout, this is not a requirement.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc28.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc28.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Membership might be limited to <a href=\"/index.php/Septon\" title=\"Septon\">septons</a> only,<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;N 1&#93;</a></sup> though women did participate alongside men in the selection of <a href=\"/index.php/Pater\" title=\"Pater\">Pater</a> as High Septon.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Most_Devout&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Before the arrival of the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">Targaryens</a>, the seat of the <a href=\"/index.php/Faith_of_the_Seven\" title=\"Faith of the Seven\">Faith of the Seven</a> was the ornate <a href=\"/index.php/Starry_Sept\" title=\"Starry Sept\">Starry Sept</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/Oldtown\" title=\"Oldtown\">Oldtown</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> Many of the Most Devout were displeased when the <a href=\"/index.php/High_Septon_(Aegon%27s_Conquest)\" title=\"High Septon (Aegon&#39;s Conquest)\">High Septon</a> advised Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Manfred_Hightower_(Aegon%27s_Conquest)\" title=\"Manfred Hightower (Aegon&#39;s Conquest)\">Manfred Hightower</a> not to oppose King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon I Targaryen\">Aegon I Targaryen</a> during <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon%27s_Conquest\" title=\"Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">Aegon's Conquest</a>, as the Faith disapproved of the <a href=\"/index.php/Incest\" title=\"Incest\">incest</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Polygamy\" title=\"Polygamy\">polygamy</a> practiced by House Targaryen.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>When King <a href=\"/index.php/Maegor_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Maegor I Targaryen\">Maegor I Targaryen</a> was approaching Oldtown during the <a href=\"/index.php/Faith_Militant_uprising\" title=\"Faith Militant uprising\">Faith Militant uprising</a>, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Martyn_Hightower\" title=\"Martyn Hightower\">Martyn Hightower</a> had his men force the Most Devout from their beds to quickly choose a new leader of the Faith after the sudden death of the <a href=\"/index.php/High_Septon_(Aenys_I)\" title=\"High Septon (Aenys I)\">High Septon</a>. <a href=\"/index.php/Pater\" title=\"Pater\">Pater</a> was chosen as the new High Septon by the assembled wise men and women.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Seventy-seven of the Most Devout escorted the <a href=\"/index.php/High_Lickspittle\" title=\"High Lickspittle\">High Septon</a> to King's Landing in <a href=\"/index.php/49_AC\" title=\"49 AC\">49&#160;AC</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_year_of_the_three_brides_-_49_ac.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_year_of_the_three_brides_-_49_ac.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> The High Septon and the Most Devout were concerned about the orthodoxy of Septon <a href=\"/index.php/Barth\" title=\"Barth\">Barth</a> when he was appointed <a href=\"/index.php/Hand_of_the_King\" title=\"Hand of the King\">Hand of the King</a> by <a href=\"/index.php/Jaehaerys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Jaehaerys I Targaryen\">Jaehaerys I Targaryen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> Barth regretted that corrupt Most Devout were easily manipulated by kings and <a href=\"/index.php/Lord\" title=\"Lord\">lords</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfaba_time_of_tesitng_-_the_realm_remade.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfaba_time_of_tesitng_-_the_realm_remade.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> Twoscore of the Most Devout died of the <a href=\"/index.php/Shivers\" title=\"Shivers\">Shivers</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Disregarding the Most Devout, <a href=\"/index.php/High_Septon_(stonemason)\" title=\"High Septon (stonemason)\">a simple stonemason</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/High_Septon_(child)\" title=\"High Septon (child)\">a young boy</a> were High Septons during the reign of King <a href=\"/index.php/Baelor_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Baelor I Targaryen\">Baelor I Targaryen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc28.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc28.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> The High Septon and the Most Devout now convene in the <a href=\"/index.php/Great_Sept_of_Baelor\" title=\"Great Sept of Baelor\">Great Sept of Baelor</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>A third of the Most Devout died during the <a href=\"/index.php/Great_Spring_Sickness\" title=\"Great Spring Sickness\">Great Spring Sickness</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_daeron_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Most_Devout&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Feast_for_Crows\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Most_Devout&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Feast for Crows\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Seven of the Most Devout attend the <a href=\"/index.php/High_Septon_(Tyrion%27s)\" title=\"High Septon (Tyrion&#39;s)\">High Septon</a> before the funeral for Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Tywin_Lannister\" title=\"Tywin Lannister\">Tywin Lannister</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup> Most Devout are among the hundreds of <a href=\"/index.php/Septons\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Septons\">septons</a> who come to mourn the late <a href=\"/index.php/Hand_of_the_King\" title=\"Hand of the King\">Hand of the King</a>, with one of them growing faint from the body's appearance and smell.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After the High Septon's death, the <a href=\"/index.php/Small_council\" title=\"Small council\">small council</a> hears that Septons <a href=\"/index.php/Torbert\" title=\"Torbert\">Torbert</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Raynard\" title=\"Raynard\">Raynard</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Ollidor\" title=\"Ollidor\">Ollidor</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Luceon_Frey\" title=\"Luceon Frey\">Luceon</a> are likely contenders to succeed him, with <a href=\"/index.php/Qyburn\" title=\"Qyburn\">Qyburn</a> reporting that Luceon hosted a dinner for thirty of the Most Devout.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc17.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_13-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc17.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-13\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The Most Devout meet in the <a href=\"/index.php/Great_Sept_of_Baelor\" title=\"Great Sept of Baelor\">Great Sept of Baelor</a> to choose the new High Septon. When Septon Luceon is nine votes away from being selected, <a href=\"/index.php/Sparrows\" title=\"Sparrows\">sparrows</a> armed with axes enter the Great Sept and force the Most Devout to choose the <a href=\"/index.php/High_Sparrow\" title=\"High Sparrow\">High Sparrow</a> as the new High Septon.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc28.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc28.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After being imprisoned by the Faith, Queen Regent <a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">Cersei Lannister</a> is asked to confess her sins by <a href=\"/index.php/Moelle\" title=\"Moelle\">Moelle</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Unella\" title=\"Unella\">Unella</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_14-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-14\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup> septas of the Most Devout.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_15-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-15\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Known_members_of_the_Most_Devout\">Known members of the Most Devout</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Most_Devout&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Known members of the Most Devout\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Historical_Most_Devout\">Historical Most Devout</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Most_Devout&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Historical Most Devout\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<ul><li>Septon <a href=\"/index.php/Eustace_(Dance_of_the_Dragons)\" title=\"Eustace (Dance of the Dragons)\">Eustace</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_16-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-16\">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Septon <a href=\"/index.php/Mattheus\" title=\"Mattheus\">Mattheus</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_year_of_the_three_brides_-_49_ac.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_year_of_the_three_brides_-_49_ac.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>The <a href=\"/index.php/High_Septon_(brother_of_Donnel_Hightower)\" title=\"High Septon (brother of Donnel Hightower)\">younger brother</a> of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Donnel_Hightower\" title=\"Donnel Hightower\">Donnel Hightower</a>, later promoted to High Septon<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabbirth.2C_death.2C_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_17-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabbirth.2C_death.2C_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-17\">&#91;16&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>One nephew of Lord Donnel Hightower<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabbirth.2C_death.2C_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_17-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabbirth.2C_death.2C_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-17\">&#91;16&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Two cousins of Lord Donnel Hightower<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabbirth.2C_death.2C_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_17-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabbirth.2C_death.2C_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-17\">&#91;16&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Most_Devout_during_A_Song_of_Ice_and_Fire\">Most Devout during <i>A Song of Ice and Fire</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Most_Devout&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Most Devout during A Song of Ice and Fire\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<ul><li>Septon <a href=\"/index.php/Raynard\" title=\"Raynard\">Raynard</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_15-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-15\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Septon <a href=\"/index.php/Torbert\" title=\"Torbert\">Torbert</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_15-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-15\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Septon <a href=\"/index.php/Luceon_Frey\" title=\"Luceon Frey\">Luceon</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_15-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-15\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Septon <a href=\"/index.php/Ollidor\" title=\"Ollidor\">Ollidor</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_15-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-15\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Septa <a href=\"/index.php/Moelle\" title=\"Moelle\">Moelle</a> (possibly)<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_15-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-15\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Septa_18-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Septa-18\">&#91;17&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Septa <a href=\"/index.php/Aglantine\" title=\"Aglantine\">Aglantine</a> (possibly)<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_15-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-15\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Septa_18-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Septa-18\">&#91;17&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Septa <a href=\"/index.php/Melicent\" title=\"Melicent\">Melicent</a> (possibly)<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_15-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-15\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Septa_18-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Septa-18\">&#91;17&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Septa <a href=\"/index.php/Unella\" title=\"Unella\">Unella</a> (possibly)<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_15-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-15\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Septa_18-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Septa-18\">&#91;17&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Most_Devout&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Spread enough <a href=\"/index.php/Gold\" title=\"Gold\">gold</a> amongst these Most Devout and they will <a href=\"/index.php/High_Septon\" title=\"High Septon\">choose me</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfaba_time_of_testing_-_the_realm_remade.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_19-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfaba_time_of_testing_-_the_realm_remade.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-19\">&#91;18&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Rego_Draz\" title=\"Rego Draz\">Rego Draz</a> to the <a href=\"/index.php/Small_council\" title=\"Small council\">small council</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Jaehaerys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Jaehaerys I Targaryen\">Jaehaerys I Targaryen</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>The <a href=\"/index.php/High_Septon_(Tyrion%27s)\" title=\"High Septon (Tyrion&#39;s)\">High Septon</a> walked slowly, leaning on a <a href=\"/index.php/Weirwood\" title=\"Weirwood\">weirwood</a> staff topped by a crystal orb. Seven of the Most Devout attended him, shimmering in cloth-of-silver.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">Cersei Lannister</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>He is utterly mad. The Most Devout must have been mad as well, to elevate <a href=\"/index.php/High_Sparrow\" title=\"High Sparrow\">this creature</a> ... mad, or terrified of <a href=\"/index.php/Sparrows\" title=\"Sparrows\">the beggars</a> at <a href=\"/index.php/Great_Sept_of_Baelor\" title=\"Great Sept of Baelor\">their doors</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc28.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc28.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">Cersei Lannister</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes\">Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Most_Devout&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Notes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Regarding the inclusion of <a href=\"/index.php/Septa\" title=\"Septa\">septas</a>, Ran explained, \"I'm inclined to think that the lack of evidence for them, other than the <a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows-Appendix\" title=\"A Feast for Crows-Appendix\">AFfC appendix</a> which seems to have been corrected in <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Appendix\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Appendix\">ADwD</a>, means no.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-Member_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Member-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Most_Devout&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Raffc8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows-Chapter_8\" title=\"A Feast for Crows-Chapter 8\">Chapter 8</a>, Jaime I.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Raffc28.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc28.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">2.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-R